cs.MA, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a method for simulating pedestrian movement in a multi-agent system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the method involves using estimated-remaining-journey-time-based dynamic assignment, which can be considered an AI technique. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the method involves simulating the behavior of pedestrians in a social network. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a possibility as the method can be used to improve the design of pedestrian spaces and improve human-computer interaction in simulations. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possibility as the method can be applied to engineering and science simulations involving pedestrian movement.
